reviews.review: Some things could have been done better and plot devices were badly used, but I think it ended the only way it could have.  Much better than TLJ.
JJ did what he could with the hand he was dealt and I really can't be mad at this Movie. Felt like a star wars movie! Very satisfied with the ending.
considering the mess rian johnson left behind JJ abrams did a great job! the movie wasn't perfect but enjoyed it very much.seen it four times so far
Ignore the reviews. A great wrap up to a decent trilogy.

Story was cliched and cringe kept trying to recapture scenes from previous Star Wars and pay homage to them but failed miserably. Action scenes were good but plot fails to deliver a satisfying ending to the saga. Felt like this movie was lazy, the writing and the plot are awful however action and cgi were amazing.

I lost all my emotional investment in Star Wars after having watched "The Last Jedi" so this film seemed to be a bit of a formality to watch. That being said, I did feel something at the very last scene of the film. I thought they nailed that pretty well despite many parts of the plot leading up to that point which I could have done without.

J.J. Abrams had an unenviably challenging task ahead of him with this movie. He had to course correct after "The Last Jedi" as well as wrap up this new trilogy and the entire Skywalker story arc! I think the movie did just about as well as it could have on both accounts. However, some parts of the plot and dialog came across as forced and quite cheesy at times. It's really too bad that some of the more interesting aspects of the movie hadn't been introduced in "The Last Jedi" and then further developed in this film.
Good ending to series with ups and downs

My teenage daughter and I are both longtime Star Wars fans. She fell asleep after the first hour, called it 'boring', and hated the ending. At least 40 minutes of it could have (and should have) been removed. There was too much time wasted with the characters running around after McGuffins instead of a focus on actual story telling and proper character development. Too many instances of deus ex machina and implausable coincidences. Stories must make sense and be consistent within the world they are set in. This one fails on both counts.  I won't be seeing it again and I see no point in wasting any money buying it on dvd.
I wish i could just delete all 3 films from existence a they are completely unnecessary.

Top 3 in the Franchise. 
I'm sure there's some plot holes to be found. But nothing glaring. 
Fixed most of what was wrong about The Last Jedi. 
A little too much too fast though.
